{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> χειμών</b>, ῶνος, ὁ, <br /> (χεῖμα) <b>winter,</b> χειμῶνος δυσθαλπέος ὅς ῥά τε ἔργων ἀνθρώπους ἀνέπαυσεν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 17.549 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; χειμῶνι <b>in winter,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 21.283; ἐν χειμῶνι 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “I.” 2.42, 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Agamemnon” 969, 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Memorabilia” 4.3.8; ἐν τῷ χ. [prev. author] “Cyr.” 8.8.17; χειμῶνος ὥρᾳ 5th-6th c.BC: Andocides Orator 1.137 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; also χειμῶνος <b>in winter-time,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Memorabilia” 3.8.9, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 415e \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; χ. μέσου <b>in</b> mid-<b>winter,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Fragmenta” 569.1; τοῦ χ. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<b>in the course of the winter,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 7.31; τοῦ αὐτοῦ χ. [prev. author] 8.30 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; διὰ χειμῶνος, διὰ τοῦ χ., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Timaeus” 74c, 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Historia Graeca (Hellenica)” 3.2.9; χειμῶνα \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<b>during winter,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Tyrannus” 1138 (variant{χειμῶνι})\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τὸν χ. <b>during</b> the <b>winter,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 3.117, 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Historia Graeca (Hellenica)” 1.4.1; τὸν δεινὸν χ. [prev. author] “An.” 7.6.9; τὸν χ. ὅλον 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Fragmenta” 345; ὁ ἀμφὶ τὸν χ. χρόνος 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 8.6.22 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ὄρος ἄβατον ὑπὸ χειμῶνος in consequence of <b>the cold weather,</b> [<a href=\"jav